00:19:50,564 --> 00:19:55,661
- What day is this?
- It's February 2. Groundhog Day.

242
00:19:59,406 --> 00:20:01,499
I thought it was yesterday.

243
00:20:23,764 --> 00:20:26,358
Did you sleep well, Mr. Connors?

244
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:28,367
Did I sleep well?

245
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:33,202
- Would you like some coffee?
- Please. I think I'll have a double.

246
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:36,037
I hope you enjoy the festivities.

247
00:20:36,109 --> 00:20:38,373
There's talk of a blizzard.

248
00:20:40,947 --> 00:20:43,381
Do you ever have deja vu?

249
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:46,385
I don't think so,
but I could check with the kitchen.

250
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:48,387
That's okay. Thank you.

251
00:20:50,190 --> 00:20:52,556
Will you be checking out today?.

252
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:58,564
I'd say the chance of departure
is 80 percent.

253
00:21:00,133 --> 00:21:02,601
Seventy-five, eighty.

254
00:21:06,773 --> 00:21:08,832
Excuse me.

255
00:21:08,909 --> 00:21:11,673
Where is everybody going?

256
00:21:11,745 --> 00:21:15,181
To Gobbler's Knob.
It's Groundhog Day.

257
00:21:15,248 --> 00:21:17,910
It's still just once a year,
isn't it?

258
00:21:30,096 --> 00:21:33,429
Phil Connors.
I thought that was you.

259
00:21:35,836 --> 00:21:39,738
Don't you say you don't remember me.
I sure as heck-fire remember you.

260
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:42,437
Ned Ryerson?

261
00:21:42,509 --> 00:21:46,104
Bing!
First shot right out of the box!

262
00:21:46,179 --> 00:21:49,114
How's It going, old buddy?.

263
00:21:49,182 --> 00:21:52,117
Actually, I'm not feeling well.
Would you excuse me?

264
00:21:52,185 --> 00:21:54,619
It's funny
you should mention your health.

265
00:21:54,688 --> 00:21:57,452
You will never guess what I do now.

266
00:21:57,524 --> 00:22:00,618
- Do you sell insurance?
- Bing again!

267
00:22:00,694 --> 00:22:02,753
You are sharp as a tack today.

268
00:22:02,829 --> 00:22:07,459
Do you have life insurance?
if you do, you could always use more.

269
00:22:07,534 --> 00:22:09,627
Right?
Who couldn't?

270
00:22:09,703 --> 00:22:15,300
You know something?
I got a feeling you ain't got any.

271
00:22:15,375 --> 00:22:19,835
- Am I right or am I right?
- I gotta go

272
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:27,812
Watch out for that first step,
It's a doozy.

273
00:22:53,079 --> 00:22:55,013
Phil, over here!

274
00:22:57,250 --> 00:23:00,014
- Where have you been?
- Rita, do me a favor.

275
00:23:00,086 --> 00:23:03,351
I need someone to give me
a good hard slap in the face.

276
00:23:04,925 --> 00:23:07,416
- How's that?
- Good.

277
00:23:07,494 --> 00:23:11,362
If you need help with the other cheek,
let me know. I'm right here.

278
00:23:12,933 --> 00:23:16,198
- Something's going on.
- Are you drunk or something?

279
00:23:16,269 --> 00:23:19,864
Drunk's more fun.
Can I be serious for a minute?

280
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:23,205
- I don't know. Can you?
- I'm being serious.

281
00:23:23,276 --> 00:23:27,337
I'm having a problem.
I may be having a problem.

282
00:23:28,782 --> 00:23:32,343
- It's groundhog time.
- I knew you would say that.

283
00:23:32,419 --> 00:23:36,048
I really feel weird.

284
00:23:36,122 --> 00:23:38,522
Let's just do this,
then we'll talk.

285
00:23:40,627 --> 00:23:42,322
On me in three.

286
00:23:42,395 --> 00:23:44,295
Two, one.

287
00:23:44,364 --> 00:23:48,391
It's Groundhog Day again.

288
00:23:48,468 --> 00:23:52,734
That must mean we're at Gobbler's Knob
waiting for the forecast...

289
00:23:52,806 --> 00:23:55,400
from the world's most famous
groundhog weatherman...

290
00:23:55,475 --> 00:23:57,067
Punxsutawney Phil...

291
00:23:57,143 --> 00:24:00,738
who's just about to tell us
how much more winter we can expect.

292
00:24:06,653 --> 00:24:08,143
This is a riot.

293
00:24:11,591 --> 00:24:12,888
Isn't he cute?

294
00:24:36,416 --> 00:24:38,941
Yeah, Sport,
I know there's a blizzard.

295
00:24:39,019 --> 00:24:42,284
When are the long-distance lines
gonna be repaired?

296
00:24:43,857 --> 00:24:47,793
What if there is no tomorrow?
There wasn't one today.

297
00:24:49,696 --> 00:24:51,129
Hello?

298
00:25:45,251 --> 00:25:48,015
Good morning.
Off to see the groundhog?

299
00:25:54,260 --> 00:25:56,751
Did you sleep well, Mr.--

300
00:26:11,778 --> 00:26:13,211
I thought--

301
00:26:14,781 --> 00:26:18,046
Don't say you don't remember me.
I sure as heck-fire remember you.

302
00:26:18,118 --> 00:26:20,382
It's me, Ned Ryerson!

303
00:26:20,453 --> 00:26:23,081
Needlenose Ned. Ned the Head.
Come on, buddy. Case Western--

304
00:26:28,628 --> 00:26:30,858
Over here!

305
00:26:30,930 --> 00:26:34,388
- Where have you been?
- Can we talk about a nonwork matter?.

306
00:26:34,467 --> 00:26:37,402
- You never talk about work
- We really have to talk. Come on.

307
00:26:37,470 --> 00:26:40,735
- It's a creative meeting. Forget lt.
- Walt a second. We've got work to do

308
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:43,571
I don't.
I've already done it twice.

309
00:26:43,643 --> 00:26:46,578
When you get finished,
meet me in the diner.

310
00:26:49,149 --> 00:26:52,243
- What's that all about?
- I don't know.

311
00:26:52,318 --> 00:26:54,047
Prima donnas.

312
00:26:57,123 --> 00:26:58,556
More coffee, hon?

313
00:26:58,625 --> 00:27:00,422
No, thanks.
Just the check, please.

314
00:27:00,493 --> 00:27:04,259
- These sticky buns are heaven.
- Aren't they?.

315
00:27:05,665 --> 00:27:08,259
Just put that anywhere, pal.

316
00:27:08,334 --> 00:27:09,767
Good save.

317
00:27:11,838 --> 00:27:14,898
Tell me why you're too sick to work,
and it better be good.

318
00:27:17,177 --> 00:27:21,273
I'm reliving the same day
over and over.

319
00:27:21,347 --> 00:27:24,282
Groundhog Day. Today.

320
00:27:24,350 --> 00:27:26,284
I'm waiting for the punch line.

321
00:27:26,352 --> 00:27:30,789
Really.
This is the third time.

322
00:27:30,857 --> 00:27:32,848
It's like yesterday never happened.

323
00:27:32,926 --> 00:27:37,056
I am racking my brain, but I can't
imagine why you'd make this up,

324
00:27:37,130 --> 00:27:40,725
I'm not making it up,
I am asking you for help!

325
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:43,200
What do you want me to do?

326
00:27:43,269 --> 00:27:46,727
I don't know! You're a producer,
come up with something.

327
00:27:46,806 --> 00:27:48,330
You want my advice?

328
00:27:48,408 --> 00:27:53,311
You should get your head examined
if you expect me to believe that story.

329
00:27:53,379 --> 00:27:55,176
Like the groundhog Phil?

330
00:27:58,551 --> 00:28:00,951
Look out for your shadow, pal.

331
00:28:01,821 --> 00:28:03,721
Morons, your bus is leaving.

332
00:28:04,791 --> 00:28:07,589
You guys ready?.
We better get going...

333
00:28:07,660 --> 00:28:10,652
- to stay ahead of the weather.
- Let's talk back in Pittsburgh.

334
00:28:10,730 --> 00:28:13,255
I'm not going back to Pittsburgh.

335
00:28:13,333 --> 00:28:15,767
- Why not?
- Because of the blizzard.

336
00:28:15,835 --> 00:28:18,167
You said that would hit Altoona.

337
00:28:18,238 --> 00:28:21,833
I know that's what I said.

338
00:28:21,908 --> 00:28:24,672
I think you need help,

339
00:28:24,744 --> 00:28:27,838
That's what I've been saying.
I need help,

340
00:28:29,415 --> 00:28:32,009
No spots, no clots...

341
00:28:32,085 --> 00:28:35,020
no tumors, no lesions....

342
00:28:35,088 --> 00:28:36,851
no aneurysms.

343
00:28:36,923 --> 00:28:38,857
None that I can see.

344
00:28:38,925 --> 00:28:42,691
If you want a CAT scan or an MRI,
you have to go into Pittsburgh.

345
00:28:42,762 --> 00:28:45,196
I can't go into Pittsburgh.

346
00:28:45,265 --> 00:28:48,530
- Why can't you go into Pittsburgh?
- There's a blizzard.

347
00:28:48,601 --> 00:28:50,535
Right. The blizzard.

348
00:28:50,603 --> 00:28:53,868
You know what you may need,
Mr. Connors?

349
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:55,874
A biopsy.

350
00:28:55,942 --> 00:28:57,375
A psychiatrist.

351
00:28:58,745 --> 00:29:03,182
That's an unusual problem,
Mr. Connors.

352
00:29:04,951 --> 00:29:08,182
Most of my work is
with couples, families.

353
00:29:08,254 --> 00:29:09,687
I have an alcoholic now.

354
00:29:11,791 --> 00:29:16,228
You went to college, right?
It wasn't veterinary psychology, was it?

355
00:29:16,296 --> 00:29:19,732
Didn't you take some course
that covered this stuff?.

356
00:29:19,799 --> 00:29:22,393
Sort of. I guess.

357
00:29:23,803 --> 00:29:25,668
Abnormal psychology.

358
00:29:25,738 --> 00:29:30,471
So, what do I do?

359
00:29:30,543 --> 00:29:32,602
I think we should meet again.

360
00:29:33,680 --> 00:29:35,580
How's tomorrow for you?

361
00:29:38,284 --> 00:29:39,717
Is that not good?

362
00:29:50,496 --> 00:29:53,431
I was in the Virgin Islands once.

363
00:29:53,499 --> 00:29:55,592
I met a girl.

364
00:29:55,668 --> 00:29:59,434
We ate lobster,
drank pina coladas.

365
00:29:59,505 --> 00:30:02,133
At sunset,
we made love like sea otters.

366
00:30:05,345 --> 00:30:08,439
That was a pretty good day.

367
00:30:08,514 --> 00:30:14,180
Why couldn't I get that day
over and over and over?.

368
00:30:14,253 --> 00:30:17,120
You know, some guys
would look at this glass...

369
00:30:17,190 --> 00:30:20,125
and they would say,
"That glass is half empty."

370
00:30:20,193 --> 00:30:23,959
Other guys would say,
"That glass is half full."

371
00:30:24,030 --> 00:30:27,625
I peg you as a "glass is half empty"
kind of guy. Am I right?

372
00:30:29,369 --> 00:30:33,135
What would you do
if you were stuck in one place...

373
00:30:33,206 --> 00:30:37,142
and every day was exactly the same,
and nothing that you did mattered?

374
00:30:39,545 --> 00:30:42,480
That sums it up for me.

375
00:30:50,056 --> 00:30:52,820
Good luck.
I'll drop you off.

376
00:30:54,894 --> 00:30:59,763
-This thing sticks. You gotta jiggle lt.
-Come on up here.

377
00:30:59,832 --> 00:31:03,996
- My gosh.
- Give me your keys, pal.

378
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:08,006
Friends don't let friends drive.
Stand up here. Take a deep breath.

379
00:31:08,074 --> 00:31:10,008
You feel okay?. Really?.

380
00:31:10,076 --> 00:31:11,509
You're all right.

381
00:31:18,084 --> 00:31:21,019
You want to throw up here
or in the car?.

382
00:31:21,087 --> 00:31:26,150
- I think both.
- Come on.

383
00:31:34,934 --> 00:31:37,368
I don't think I should be driving.

384
00:31:37,437 --> 00:31:40,702
I don't either.
Watch your head.

385
00:31:40,773 --> 00:31:43,037
Watch your knees.
Don't break anything.

386
00:31:43,109 --> 00:31:46,442
All right.
Let's not forget seat belts.

387
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:51,542
Who else could go
for some flapjacks right now?

388
00:31:56,556 --> 00:31:58,717
Let me ask you guys a question.

389
00:31:58,791 --> 00:32:03,057
- Shoot.
- What if there were no tomorrow?

390
00:32:03,129 --> 00:32:07,065
No tomorrow? That would mean
there would be no consequences.

391
00:32:07,133 --> 00:32:11,467
There would be no hangovers.
We could do whatever we wanted!

392
00:32:12,638 --> 00:32:17,405
That's true.
We could do whatever we want.

393
00:32:22,982 --> 00:32:26,645
If we wanted to hit mailboxes,
we could let Ralph drive!

394
00:32:33,493 --> 00:32:36,257
- I think they want you to stop,
- Hang on.

395
00:32:41,801 --> 00:32:44,031
It's the same thing
your whole life:.

396
00:32:44,103 --> 00:32:47,402
"Clean up your room." "Stand up
straight." "Pick up your feet."

397
00:32:47,473 --> 00:32:52,001
"Take it like a man."
"Be nice to your sister."

398
00:32:52,078 --> 00:32:54,603
"Don't mix beer and wine, ever."

399
00:32:56,182 --> 00:32:58,616
"Don't drive
on the railroad tracks."

400
00:32:58,684 --> 00:33:01,482
Phil, that's one
I happen to agree with.

401
00:33:10,863 --> 00:33:13,297
I don't know, Gus.

402
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:18,861
Sometimes I think you just have
to take the big chances.

403
00:33:18,938 --> 00:33:21,429
This is the police!
Pullover immediately!

404
00:33:22,708 --> 00:33:24,938
We're talking in here.

405
00:33:30,049 --> 00:33:32,108
I'm betting he'll swerve first.

406
00:33:46,232 --> 00:33:49,633
I'm not gonna live
by their rules anymore.

407
00:33:49,702 --> 00:33:54,196
- I noticed that.
- You make choices and live with them.

408
00:34:08,421 --> 00:34:09,911
My knee.

409
00:34:12,758 --> 00:34:14,692
Let me handle this.

410
00:34:16,262 --> 00:34:20,028
Three cheeseburgers,
two large fries...

411
00:34:20,099 --> 00:34:22,192
two chocolate shake
and one large Coke.

412
00:34:22,268 --> 00:34:26,500
- And some flapjacks.
- Too early for flapjacks?

413
00:34:42,455 --> 00:34:44,389
Rise and shine, campers!

414
00:34:44,457 --> 00:34:47,221
Don't forget your booties
because it's cold out there today!

415
00:34:47,293 --> 00:34:52,424
It's cold out there every day.
What is this, Miami Beach? Not hardly.

416
00:34:56,802 --> 00:34:58,565
Slept like a baby .
Thank you.

417
00:34:58,638 --> 00:35:01,232
- I'd love some of your coffee.
- I hope--

418
00:35:01,307 --> 00:35:05,073
Flurries moving in later, but
the blizzard will hit outside of town.

419
00:35:05,144 --> 00:35:08,739
Mrs. Lancaster, was anybody
looking for me here this morning?

420
00:35:08,814 --> 00:35:13,080
Perhaps a state official?
Maybe a blue hat, gun, nightstick?

421
00:35:13,152 --> 00:35:15,746
No one like that.
will there be?

422
00:35:15,821 --> 00:35:17,254
Apparently not.

423
00:35:19,659 --> 00:35:22,753
Hold my room for me, please.
I'm staying an extra day.

424
00:35:28,834 --> 00:35:30,825
Catch you tomorrow, Pops.

425
00:36:10,042 --> 00:36:13,307
I like to see a man of advancing years
throwing caution to the wind.

426
00:36:13,379 --> 00:36:16,473
It's inspiring, in a way.

427
00:36:16,549 --> 00:36:19,109
My years are not advancing
as fast as you might think.

428
00:36:19,185 --> 00:36:20,618
More coffee, hon?

429
00:36:20,686 --> 00:36:22,449
Just keep It coming, please.

430
00:36:22,521 --> 00:36:23,954
Sure thing.

431
00:36:25,725 --> 00:36:28,319
Just put that anywhere, pal.

432
00:36:28,394 --> 00:36:29,827
Good save.

433
00:36:31,897 --> 00:36:35,560
Don't you worry about cholesterol,
lung cancer, love handles?

434
00:36:37,737 --> 00:36:39,568
I don't worry
about anything anymore.

435
00:36:39,638 --> 00:36:42,402
What make you so special?
Everybody worries about something.

436
00:36:42,475 --> 00:36:47,469
That's exactly what make me so special.
I don't even have to floss.

437
00:36:56,722 --> 00:36:58,155
What?

438
00:36:59,759 --> 00:37:03,957
"The wretch,
concentered all in self...

439
00:37:04,029 --> 00:37:06,497
Living,
shall forfeit fair renown...

440
00:37:06,565 --> 00:37:09,830
And, doubly dying,
shall go down...

441
00:37:09,902 --> 00:37:13,201
To the vile dust,
from whence he sprung...

442
00:37:13,272 --> 00:37:17,333
Unwept, unhonor'd, and unsung."

443
00:37:17,409 --> 00:37:19,877
Sir Walter Scott.

444
00:37:22,848 --> 00:37:26,716
- You don't like poetry?.
- I love poetry.

445
00:37:26,786 --> 00:37:30,222
I just thought that was Willard Scott.
I was confused.

446
00:37:30,289 --> 00:37:33,053
Do you think I'm acting like this
because I'm egocentric?

447
00:37:33,125 --> 00:37:36,390
I know you're egocentric.
It's your defining characteristic.

448
00:37:38,631 --> 00:37:42,226
Are you guys ready?. We better get going
to stay ahead of the weather.

449
00:37:42,301 --> 00:37:46,067
Thanks, Larry.
Would you like a doggie bag?

450
00:37:46,138 --> 00:37:50,074
- I'll stay here and finish.
- I thought you hated this town.

451
00:37:50,142 --> 00:37:53,236
It's beginning to grow on me.

452
00:37:53,312 --> 00:37:54,870
Larry, quit staring.

453
00:37:54,947 --> 00:37:56,574
These are excellent.

454
00:38:08,627 --> 00:38:11,926
Did you see the groundhog
this morning?

455
00:38:11,997 --> 00:38:14,431
I never miss lt.

456
00:38:14,500 --> 00:38:16,434
What's your name?

457
00:38:17,837 --> 00:38:20,101
Nancy Taylor.
And you are?

458
00:38:20,172 --> 00:38:22,936
- What high school did you go to?
- What?

459
00:38:23,008 --> 00:38:27,604
- High school.
- Lincoln, in Pittsburgh.

460
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:31,616
- Who are you?
- Who was your senior English teacher?.

461
00:38:31,684 --> 00:38:33,948
Are you kidding?

462
00:38:34,019 --> 00:38:37,785
- Your 1 2th-grade English teacher was--
- Mrs. Walsh.

463
00:38:37,857 --> 00:38:42,624
Nancy. Lincoln. Walsh.
Thanks very much.

464
00:39:04,049 --> 00:39:06,643
Lincoln High School.

465
00:39:06,719 --> 00:39:09,483
I sat next to you
in Mrs. Walsh's English class.

466
00:39:09,555 --> 00:39:11,489
I'm sorry.

467
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:17,620
- That's amazing.
- You don't remember me, do you?

468
00:39:20,199 --> 00:39:21,860
I even asked you to the prom.

469
00:39:25,037 --> 00:39:27,699
I was short,
and I've sprouted.

470
00:39:30,910 --> 00:39:33,845
Gosh! How are you?

471
00:39:34,713 --> 00:39:37,580
Great.
You look terrific.

472
00:39:37,650 --> 00:39:40,175
You look very terrific.

473
00:39:42,421 --> 00:39:46,016
- I have to do this report.
- Are you a reporter?.

474
00:39:46,091 --> 00:39:49,026
I'm a weatherman
with Channel 9 Pittsburgh.

475
00:39:49,094 --> 00:39:51,289
I should have known.
That's great!

476
00:39:51,363 --> 00:39:53,160
Maybe later we could--

477
00:39:53,232 --> 00:39:54,699
Whatever.

478
00:39:54,767 --> 00:39:58,032
Stay right here.
Promise me?

479
00:39:58,103 --> 00:40:00,537
I'll be right back.
Wish me luck.

480
00:40:00,606 --> 00:40:02,039
Good luck!

481
00:40:27,633 --> 00:40:29,225
Who's Rita?

482
00:40:29,301 --> 00:40:31,235
How should I know?

483
00:40:31,303 --> 00:40:34,067
Is this some kind
of one-night stand?

484
00:40:34,139 --> 00:40:37,074
On the contrary, Nancy.
I love you.

485
00:40:37,142 --> 00:40:40,236
I've always loved you.

