01:00:19,323 --> 01:00:20,881
I have to stop him.

730
01:00:23,394 --> 01:00:25,225
Real good, Phil.

731
01:00:27,331 --> 01:00:28,923
He's crazy.

732
01:00:33,571 --> 01:00:36,836
I'm worried. I think there's something
really wrong with Phil.

733
01:00:36,908 --> 01:00:39,536
There's a lot of things
really wrong with Phil.

734
01:00:43,714 --> 01:00:46,012
I've come to the end of me.

735
01:00:46,083 --> 01:00:49,450
There's no way out now.

736
01:00:49,520 --> 01:00:52,956
I just want you to remember
we had a beautiful day together once.

737
01:00:56,294 --> 01:00:59,821
All right, little fella.
Good job.

738
01:00:59,897 --> 01:01:02,525
- He smiled at me. Did you see that?
- I believe he did.

739
01:01:04,168 --> 01:01:06,329
Okay, little fella.
There you go

740
01:01:08,873 --> 01:01:11,307
Hl, mister.
Something I can do you for?.

741
01:01:13,945 --> 01:01:15,879
What are you doing?

742
01:01:20,585 --> 01:01:22,712
Jake, get the word out!
Somebody kidnapped Phil!

743
01:01:22,787 --> 01:01:24,379
We're going after him!

744
01:01:30,861 --> 01:01:33,887
Why would anybody steal a groundhog?

745
01:01:33,965 --> 01:01:36,957
I can probably think
of a couple of reasons. Pervert.

746
01:02:02,760 --> 01:02:06,321
- He must have just snapped!
- This should be good.

747
01:02:08,766 --> 01:02:11,701
What is he doing?
What can he be thinking?

748
01:02:11,769 --> 01:02:14,203
That's not bad
for a quadruped.

749
01:02:14,272 --> 01:02:18,106
You gotta check your mirrors,
Just the side of your eye.

750
01:02:24,048 --> 01:02:25,777
That's lt.

751
01:02:25,850 --> 01:02:28,478
They're chasing us!
Come on, make It fun!

752
01:02:36,961 --> 01:02:39,759
Don't drive angry.

753
01:02:59,750 --> 01:03:04,380
Hot dog! There's no way out except
the way we came in. We got him now!

754
01:03:23,341 --> 01:03:26,139
- What is he doing?
- I don't know.

755
01:03:30,247 --> 01:03:33,273
If you gotta shoot, aim high.
I don't wanna hit the groundhog.

756
01:03:37,621 --> 01:03:39,816
We mustn't keep
our public waiting.

757
01:03:43,027 --> 01:03:44,494
It's show time.

758
01:03:50,768 --> 01:03:53,202
All right, on me, Larry,
in three!

759
01:03:54,638 --> 01:03:58,199
Two, one.

760
01:04:15,059 --> 01:04:16,526
He might be okay.

761
01:04:21,232 --> 01:04:23,723
Probably not now.

762
01:04:39,450 --> 01:04:41,475
Nuts.

763
01:04:48,526 --> 01:04:51,859
Did you sleep well, Mr. Connors?

764
01:04:51,929 --> 01:04:55,558
Would you like some toast?

765
01:05:13,451 --> 01:05:17,012
- What's going on?
- My God.

766
01:05:49,286 --> 01:05:50,719
That's him.

767
01:05:53,724 --> 01:05:57,387
He was a really great guy.

768
01:05:57,461 --> 01:06:00,294
I really liked him a lot.

769
01:06:07,771 --> 01:06:07,905
I'm sorry.
What was that again?

770
01:06:07,905 --> 01:06:09,998
I'm sorry.
What was that again?

771
01:06:10,074 --> 01:06:13,168
- I'm a god!
- You're a god?

772
01:06:13,244 --> 01:06:16,611
I'm a god.
I'm not the God, I don't think.

773
01:06:16,680 --> 01:06:19,274
Because you survived a car wreck?

774
01:06:19,350 --> 01:06:20,942
You ready to order?.

775
01:06:21,018 --> 01:06:24,181
I didn't just survive a wreck.
I wasn't just blown up yesterday.

776
01:06:24,255 --> 01:06:27,122
I have been stabbed,
shot poisoned...

777
01:06:27,191 --> 01:06:30,126
frozen, hung, electrocuted...

778
01:06:30,194 --> 01:06:32,458
- and burned.
- Really?.

779
01:06:32,530 --> 01:06:37,297
Every morning I wake up fine,
not a dent in the fender.

780
01:06:37,368 --> 01:06:41,304
- I am an immortal.
- Special today is blueberry waffles.

781
01:06:41,372 --> 01:06:43,363
Why are you telling me this?

782
01:06:43,440 --> 01:06:45,772
Because I want you
to believe in me.

783
01:06:45,843 --> 01:06:50,940
You're not a god. Believe me. This is
12 years of Catholic school talking.

784
01:06:51,015 --> 01:06:53,449
I could come back
if you're not ready.

785
01:06:53,517 --> 01:06:55,815
How do you know I'm not a god?

786
01:06:55,886 --> 01:06:59,720
Please!
Because It's not possible!

787
01:06:59,790 --> 01:07:02,850
- I'll come back.
- Doris!

788
01:07:06,730 --> 01:07:09,494
This is Doris. Her brother-in-law,
Carl, owns this diner.

789
01:07:09,567 --> 01:07:14,129
She's worked here since she was 1 7.
She wants to see Paris before she dies.

790
01:07:14,204 --> 01:07:16,604
- Boy, would l!
- What are you doing?

791
01:07:16,674 --> 01:07:20,235
- Debbie Klelser and her fiance, Fred.
- Do I know you?

792
01:07:20,311 --> 01:07:23,439
They're supposed to be married this
afternoon, but Debbie is reconsidering.

793
01:07:23,514 --> 01:07:26,483
- What?
- Lovely ring.

794
01:07:26,550 --> 01:07:28,745
This is Bill who's been a walter
for three years...

795
01:07:28,819 --> 01:07:31,310
since he left Penn State
and had to get work

796
01:07:31,388 --> 01:07:34,221
He like the town, paints toy soldiers,
and he's gay.

797
01:07:34,291 --> 01:07:36,156
I am.

798
01:07:36,226 --> 01:07:39,320
This is Gus. He hates his life here
and wishes he'd stayed in the Navy.

799
01:07:39,396 --> 01:07:42,058
I could have retired on half pay
after 20 years.

800
01:07:42,132 --> 01:07:44,191
Is this some kind of trick?

801
01:07:44,268 --> 01:07:47,169
Maybe the real God uses tricks.
Maybe He's not omnipotent.

802
01:07:47,237 --> 01:07:50,365
He's just been around so long,
He knows everything.

803
01:07:50,441 --> 01:07:51,874
- Who's that?
- This is Tom.

804
01:07:51,942 --> 01:07:54,172
He worked in the coal mine
till they closed It down.

805
01:07:54,244 --> 01:07:55,677
- Her?.
- Alice.

806
01:07:55,746 --> 01:07:58,374
She came from Ireland as a baby
and lived in Erie most of her life.

807
01:07:58,449 --> 01:08:00,576
- He's right.
- Nancy.

808
01:08:00,651 --> 01:08:05,384
She works in the dress shop and make
chipmunk noises when she gets excited.

809
01:08:05,456 --> 01:08:07,390
- It's true.
- How do you know these people?

810
01:08:07,458 --> 01:08:12,259
I know everything. I n five seconds,
a walter will drop a tray of dishes.

811
01:08:12,329 --> 01:08:15,127
- Five, four, three, two, one.
- This is nuts.

812
01:08:17,901 --> 01:08:19,334
That's enough.

813
01:08:20,971 --> 01:08:24,771
- Do you know me too?
- I know all about you.

814
01:08:24,842 --> 01:08:27,640
You like producing, but you're hoping
for more than Channel 9 Pittsburgh.

815
01:08:27,711 --> 01:08:30,236
Everyone knows that.

816
01:08:30,314 --> 01:08:33,579
You like boats, but not the ocean.

817
01:08:33,651 --> 01:08:37,212
You go to a mountain lake in the summer
with your family.

818
01:08:37,287 --> 01:08:39,312
There's a long, wooden dock
and a boathouse...

819
01:08:39,390 --> 01:08:41,415
with boards missing
from the roof....

820
01:08:41,492 --> 01:08:44,825
and a place you used to crawl
underneath to be alone.

821
01:08:44,895 --> 01:08:49,264
You're a sucker for French poetry
and rhinestones.

822
01:08:49,333 --> 01:08:51,096
You're very generous.

823
01:08:51,168 --> 01:08:54,035
You're kind to strangers
and children.

824
01:08:54,104 --> 01:08:56,937
And when you stand in the snow,
you look like an angel.

825
01:08:57,007 --> 01:08:58,941
How are you doing this?

826
01:09:00,077 --> 01:09:04,946
I wake up every day right here...

827
01:09:05,015 --> 01:09:08,507
In Punxsutawney,
and It's always February 2.

828
01:09:09,586 --> 01:09:12,020
There's nothing
I can do about lt.

829
01:09:12,856 --> 01:09:16,019
If you still doubt me...

830
01:09:16,093 --> 01:09:18,561
In ten seconds...

831
01:09:18,629 --> 01:09:22,326
Larry will come through that door
and take you away from me...

832
01:09:22,399 --> 01:09:25,129
but you can't let him.

833
01:09:25,202 --> 01:09:28,171
Please believe me.
You've got to believe me.

834
01:09:33,343 --> 01:09:37,279
You ready?. We better get going if we're
going to stay ahead of the weather.

835
01:09:37,347 --> 01:09:39,611
What's that?

836
01:09:48,125 --> 01:09:50,059
Maybe It really is happening.

837
01:09:50,127 --> 01:09:52,220
How else could you know so much?

838
01:09:52,296 --> 01:09:54,787
There is no way.
I'm not that smart.

839
01:09:55,966 --> 01:09:58,400
Maybe I should spend the day
with you...

840
01:09:58,469 --> 01:10:01,996
as an objective witness,
Just to see what happens.

841
01:10:02,072 --> 01:10:04,802
This sounds
like a science project.

842
01:10:05,776 --> 01:10:08,472
Concentrate.
You gotta want lt.

843
01:10:12,149 --> 01:10:15,846
It's more in the wrist than the finger.
It's just gotta--

844
01:10:24,161 --> 01:10:26,095
Be the hat! Come on! Go!

845
01:10:26,163 --> 01:10:28,097
It would take me a year
to get good at this.

846
01:10:28,165 --> 01:10:32,693
Six months. Four to five hours a day,
and you'd be an expert.

847
01:10:32,770 --> 01:10:35,136
Is this what you do
with eternity?.

848
01:10:35,205 --> 01:10:36,832
Now you know.

849
01:10:38,242 --> 01:10:40,233
That's not the worst part.

850
01:10:40,310 --> 01:10:42,244
What's the worst part?

851
01:10:42,312 --> 01:10:47,113
The worst part is that tomorrow you
will have forgotten all about this...

852
01:10:47,184 --> 01:10:50,381
and you'll treat me
like a jerk again.

853
01:10:50,454 --> 01:10:54,049
- It's all right. I am a jerk
- You're not.

854
01:10:54,124 --> 01:10:56,183
It doesn't make any difference.

855
01:10:56,260 --> 01:11:00,890
I've killed myself so many times,
I don't even exist anymore.

856
01:11:00,964 --> 01:11:04,297
Sometimes I wish
I had a thousand lifetimes.

857
01:11:04,368 --> 01:11:07,997
I don't know, Phil.
Maybe It's not a curse.

858
01:11:08,071 --> 01:11:10,596
It just depends on
how you look at lt.

859
01:11:12,376 --> 01:11:14,571
Gosh, you're an upbeat lady!

860
01:11:17,815 --> 01:11:22,309
- It's been a really nice day for me.
- Me too.

861
01:11:22,386 --> 01:11:27,414
Maybe, if it's not too boring,
we could do It again sometime.

862
01:11:27,491 --> 01:11:29,425
I hope so

863
01:11:41,371 --> 01:11:42,929
You're still here.

864
01:11:44,541 --> 01:11:48,477
I thought you were supposed
to disappear or I was or something!

865
01:11:48,545 --> 01:11:51,036
Not until 6:00.

866
01:11:51,114 --> 01:11:52,741
You rat!

867
01:11:52,816 --> 01:11:54,545
I never said midnight.

868
01:11:54,618 --> 01:11:59,578
- You knew I was waiting for midnight!
- Does this mean you're gonna leave?

869
01:12:03,060 --> 01:12:04,493
Good.

870
01:12:15,205 --> 01:12:16,638
I'm sorry.

871
01:12:18,408 --> 01:12:21,571
It's all right.
You can fall asleep,

872
01:12:21,645 --> 01:12:25,979
I promise
I won't touch you, much.

873
01:12:27,251 --> 01:12:30,652
That's all right.
I'm not tired.

874
01:12:30,721 --> 01:12:32,746
What were you saying?

875
01:12:33,957 --> 01:12:37,324
I think the last thing
that you heard was...

876
01:12:37,394 --> 01:12:39,919
"Only God can make a tree."

877
01:12:39,997 --> 01:12:41,430
Really?.

878
01:13:19,703 --> 01:13:21,637
What I wanted to say was...

879
01:13:23,674 --> 01:13:29,044
I think you're the kindest, sweetest,
prettiest person...

880
01:13:29,112 --> 01:13:31,205
I've ever met in my life.

881
01:13:32,683 --> 01:13:35,413
I've never seen anyone...

882
01:13:35,485 --> 01:13:37,885
that's nicer to people
than you are.

883
01:13:51,134 --> 01:13:54,001
The first time I saw you...

884
01:13:54,071 --> 01:13:57,563
something happened to me.

885
01:13:57,641 --> 01:14:00,075
I never told you, but...

886
01:14:03,213 --> 01:14:07,741
I knew that I wanted
to hold you as hard as I could.

887
01:14:20,597 --> 01:14:23,760
I don't deserve someone like you.

888
01:14:26,870 --> 01:14:30,169
But if I ever could...

889
01:14:30,240 --> 01:14:32,572
I swear I would love you...

890
01:14:32,642 --> 01:14:34,769
for the rest of my life.

891
01:14:39,383 --> 01:14:41,442
Did you say something?

892
01:14:46,957 --> 01:14:48,390
Good night.

893
01:16:00,964 --> 01:16:03,398
Who wants coffee?
Get It while It's hot.

894
01:16:03,467 --> 01:16:05,230
Thanks, Phil.

895
01:16:05,302 --> 01:16:10,330
- Larry?. Skim milk, two sugars.
- Thanks, Phil.

896
01:16:10,407 --> 01:16:12,967
- Pastry?.
- We're just setting up,

897
01:16:13,043 --> 01:16:14,943
Take your pick.

898
01:16:16,213 --> 01:16:18,272
Thanks. Raspberry. Great.

899
01:16:18,348 --> 01:16:21,875
I was just talking with Buster Green,
the head groundhog honcho

900
01:16:21,952 --> 01:16:24,944
He said if we set up over here,
we might get a better shot.

901
01:16:25,021 --> 01:16:27,683
- What do you think?
- Sounds good.

902
01:16:27,757 --> 01:16:29,224
What do you think?

903
01:16:30,527 --> 01:16:32,461
Let's go for lt.

904
01:16:32,529 --> 01:16:35,521
- Good work
- Maybe we'll get lucky .

905
01:16:35,599 --> 01:16:37,533
Let me help you
with the heavy stuff..

906
01:16:39,302 --> 01:16:42,237
You got your coffee.
I'll get lt.

907
01:16:43,340 --> 01:16:45,274
We never talk.
Do you have kids?

908
01:17:19,976 --> 01:17:21,910
I'd like a piano lesson, please.

909
01:17:21,978 --> 01:17:26,415
I'm with a student now. If you come
back tomorrow, I can squeeze you in.

910
01:17:26,483 --> 01:17:29,646
I kind of want to get started.
I could give you $1 ,000.

911
01:17:31,888 --> 01:17:33,321
Come on in.

912
01:17:53,043 --> 01:17:55,136
Good morning!
Off to see the groundhog?

913
01:17:58,281 --> 01:18:00,806
You think It will be
an early spring?

914
01:18:00,884 --> 01:18:03,409
"Winter slumbering in the open air...

915
01:18:03,486 --> 01:18:05,420
wears on his smiling face...

916
01:18:05,488 --> 01:18:07,456
a dream of spring."

917
01:18:49,532 --> 01:18:50,965
How's she look?

918
01:18:51,034 --> 01:18:53,594
- Great.
- Thank you.

919
01:18:53,670 --> 01:18:55,638
Did you know
he could ice sculpt?

920
01:19:11,421 --> 01:19:14,515
Not bad.
You say this is your first lesson?

921
01:19:15,458 --> 01:19:18,188
My father was a piano mover.

922
01:19:24,734 --> 01:19:26,895
I thought It was you.

923
01:19:30,807 --> 01:19:33,435
I have missed you so much.

924
01:19:37,414 --> 01:19:41,350
I don't know where you're headed,
but can you call in sick?

925
01:19:44,754 --> 01:19:47,450
I gotta get going.

926
01:19:47,524 --> 01:19:49,583
It's good to see you.

927
01:20:07,677 --> 01:20:09,838
Hello, father.

928
01:20:09,913 --> 01:20:13,405
Let's get you someplace warm.

929
01:20:13,483 --> 01:20:14,916
Remember me?

930
01:20:20,056 --> 01:20:23,116
Excuse me, sir. Are you the one
who brought the old man in?

931
01:20:23,193 --> 01:20:25,184
How is he?

932
01:20:25,261 --> 01:20:27,627
He just passed away.

933
01:20:28,865 --> 01:20:30,799
What did he die of?.

934
01:20:30,867 --> 01:20:34,132
He was just old.
It was just his time.

935
01:20:36,940 --> 01:20:40,000
- I want to see his chart. Excuse me.
- Sir!

936
01:20:40,076 --> 01:20:42,237
You can't come in here.

937
01:20:42,312 --> 01:20:44,974
This is a restricted area.

938
01:20:53,990 --> 01:20:56,220
Where's the chart?

939
01:20:56,292 --> 01:20:59,489
Sometimes people just die.

940
01:20:59,562 --> 01:21:01,496
Not today.

941
01:21:13,343 --> 01:21:15,277
It's hard down there
at the bottom.

942
01:21:18,515 --> 01:21:21,177
- Here you go
- Thank you.

943
01:21:25,522 --> 01:21:27,513
Come on, Dad!
Come on, Pop!

944
01:21:31,561 --> 01:21:34,189
Breathe, Pop!

945
01:22:00,723 --> 01:22:03,317
When Chekhov
saw the long winter...

946
01:22:03,393 --> 01:22:07,295
he saw a winter bleak and dark
and bereft of hope.

947
01:22:07,363 --> 01:22:12,300
Yet we know that winter is just
another step in the cycle of life.

948
01:22:12,368 --> 01:22:16,236
But standing here
among the people of Punxsutawney...

949
01:22:16,306 --> 01:22:19,036
and basking in the warmth
of their hearths and hearts...

950
01:22:20,143 --> 01:22:22,407
I couldn't imagine a better fate...

951
01:22:22,479 --> 01:22:25,744
than a long and lustrous winter.

952
01:22:25,815 --> 01:22:28,807
From Punxsutawney,
It's Phil Connors.

953
01:22:28,885 --> 01:22:30,318
So long.

954
01:22:32,021 --> 01:22:33,955
Very nice speech, Phil.

955
01:22:34,023 --> 01:22:36,355
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

956
01:22:36,426 --> 01:22:39,657
- How was that for you two?
- Man, you touched me.

957
01:22:39,729 --> 01:22:41,663
- Thanks, Larry.
- Thank you.

958
01:22:43,199 --> 01:22:45,463
I gotta go

959
01:22:45,535 --> 01:22:49,733
That was surprising.
I didn't know you were so versatile.

960
01:22:49,806 --> 01:22:51,740
I surprise myself sometimes.

961
01:22:51,808 --> 01:22:53,867
Would you like
to get some coffee?

962
01:22:53,943 --> 01:22:57,936
I'd love to. Can I have a rain check?
I've got some errands to run.

963
01:23:01,618 --> 01:23:05,554
What errands?
I thought we were going back.

964
01:23:15,231 --> 01:23:16,994
Hold it, fella!

965
01:23:23,806 --> 01:23:26,639
What do you say?.

966
01:23:26,709 --> 01:23:30,145
You little brat.
You have never thanked me!

967
01:23:30,213 --> 01:23:33,478
I'll see you tomorrow, maybe!

968
01:23:40,590 --> 01:23:43,320
- Now what?
- You've totaled lt.

969
01:23:43,393 --> 01:23:48,490
It's only a flat tire.
Now just be patient. Just cool it!

970
01:23:48,565 --> 01:23:52,467
- It's an earthquake!
- It's not an earthquake!

971
01:23:52,535 --> 01:23:53,968
What is it?

972
01:23:57,240 --> 01:23:59,333
Thank you, young man.

973
01:24:00,476 --> 01:24:02,967
It's nothing.
I had the tire and the jack.

974
01:24:03,046 --> 01:24:05,742
Just be comfortable.
Be a minute.

975
01:24:05,815 --> 01:24:07,339
Who is that?

976
01:24:07,417 --> 01:24:10,181
Must be from the motor club.

977
01:24:11,688 --> 01:24:14,384
- My God! He's having a heart attack!
- What should I do?

978
01:24:14,457 --> 01:24:17,858
- Call an ambulance, a lawyer, a doctor!
- Mom, I don't think he's breathing!

979
01:24:25,802 --> 01:24:27,736
I think that did lt.

980
01:24:31,174 --> 01:24:34,109
If you're gonna eat steak,
get some sharper teeth.

981
01:24:34,177 --> 01:24:36,873
- Enjoy your lunch.
- Thank you.

982
01:24:36,946 --> 01:24:39,676
Who was that? I'm fine.

983
01:24:39,749 --> 01:24:42,547
- Are you sure?
- Oh, yes. Eat.

984
01:24:46,956 --> 01:24:49,618
People just don't understand
what is involved in this.

985
01:24:49,692 --> 01:24:51,626
This is an art form.

986
01:24:51,694 --> 01:24:54,424
You know, I think most people
Just think that...

987
01:24:54,497 --> 01:24:57,660
I hold the camera
and point It at stuff..

988
01:24:57,734 --> 01:25:00,202
There is a lot more to It
than just that.

989
01:25:02,105 --> 01:25:05,404
Would you be at all interested
in seeing the inside of the van?

990
01:25:05,475 --> 01:25:09,377
You know, I really have to get back
to the party.

991
01:25:09,445 --> 01:25:13,404
Great idea. I'll go with you.
Let me just drop a tip here.

992
01:25:20,523 --> 01:25:23,390
How are you?
Rita, this is Nancy.

993
01:25:23,459 --> 01:25:25,893
We were just going
to the party.

994
01:25:25,962 --> 01:25:27,896
- You going?
- Sounds like fun.

995
01:25:27,964 --> 01:25:30,558
Maybe we should call Phil.

996
01:25:30,633 --> 01:25:32,692
- I think he's already in there.
- Great.

997
01:27:29,385 --> 01:27:32,218
- Isn't he good?
- He's great!

998
01:27:32,288 --> 01:27:34,222
He's my student.

999
01:27:36,526 --> 01:27:38,460
I'm so proud.

1000
01:27:39,595 --> 01:27:41,028
Thank you.

1001
01:27:41,998 --> 01:27:44,091
Welcome to our party.

1002
01:27:44,167 --> 01:27:47,933
-I didn't know you could play like that.
-I'm versatile.

1003
01:27:55,878 --> 01:27:58,904
It's that nice, young man
from the motor club.

1004
01:27:58,981 --> 01:28:02,280
- Thank you again.
- It's nothing, ladles.

1005
01:28:02,351 --> 01:28:05,752
He's the fastest jack
in Jefferson County.

1006
01:28:08,124 --> 01:28:10,058
What was that all about?

1007
01:28:10,126 --> 01:28:13,152
I really don't know.
They've been hitting on me all night.

1008
01:28:14,030 --> 01:28:15,463
There you are.

1009
01:28:17,333 --> 01:28:20,734
I never thanked you properly
for what you did for Buster.

1010
01:28:20,803 --> 01:28:23,169
He would have choked for sure.

1011
01:28:23,239 --> 01:28:27,073
He may have.
He was trying to swallow a whole cow.

1012
01:28:27,143 --> 01:28:31,239
- I owe you one, buddy.
- Hang onto him, dear. He's a real find.

1013
01:28:34,116 --> 01:28:37,643
- What did you do today?.
- Same old, same old.

1014
01:28:43,292 --> 01:28:45,021
Excuse me.

1015
01:28:45,094 --> 01:28:47,028
Fred, how was the wedding?

1016
01:28:47,096 --> 01:28:50,293
I just wanted to thank you
for making Debbie go through with lt.

1017
01:28:50,366 --> 01:28:53,529
All I did was fan the flame
of her passion for you.

1018
01:28:53,603 --> 01:28:56,197
You are the best.

1019
01:28:56,272 --> 01:28:59,503
Rita,
this is Debbie and Fred Klelser.

1020
01:28:59,575 --> 01:29:02,840
- Here you go, kids. Congratulations.
- What is this?

1021
01:29:02,912 --> 01:29:06,040
No way!

1022
01:29:06,115 --> 01:29:07,548
Wrestlemania!

1023
01:29:10,152 --> 01:29:13,212
How did you know?
We're gonna be in Pittsburgh anyway!

1024
01:29:13,289 --> 01:29:17,157
- Thank you! You're a real pal!
- This is the best!

1025
01:29:22,164 --> 01:29:25,930
- I don't understand.
- I guess not.

1026
01:29:26,002 --> 01:29:28,470
How does everyone know you?
You only come here once a year.

1027
01:29:28,537 --> 01:29:31,097
You seem like the most popular person
in town.

1028
01:29:31,173 --> 01:29:33,505
Excuse me. Dr. Connors?

1029
01:29:33,576 --> 01:29:36,374
I want to thank you
for fixing Felix's back.

1030
01:29:36,445 --> 01:29:38,811
He can even help
around the house again.

1031
01:29:38,881 --> 01:29:41,349
I'm sorry to hear that, Felix.

1032
01:29:43,853 --> 01:29:45,787
"Dr. Connors"?

1033
01:29:45,855 --> 01:29:48,415
It's kind of an honorary title.

1034
01:29:48,491 --> 01:29:51,289
- What is going on?
- I really don't know.

1035
01:29:51,360 --> 01:29:54,591
There is something
going on with you.

1036
01:29:54,664 --> 01:29:56,757
Would you like the long version
or the short one?

1037
01:29:56,832 --> 01:29:59,596
Let's start with the short
and go from there.

1038
01:30:05,341 --> 01:30:08,105
Okay, folks. Attention.

1039
01:30:08,177 --> 01:30:11,510
Time for the big bachelor auction.
You all know the rules.

1040
01:30:11,580 --> 01:30:14,048
All the eligible bachelors
come down in front...

1041
01:30:14,116 --> 01:30:17,381
and you ladles bid on them!

1042
01:30:17,453 --> 01:30:21,514
You get to do whatever you want
with them. No questions asked!

1043
01:30:21,590 --> 01:30:24,855
I don't want to know about it,
as long as It's legal!

1044
01:30:24,927 --> 01:30:28,727
Get out your pocketbooks and remember,
It's all for charity!

1045
01:30:31,667 --> 01:30:34,966
What are you doing down here?
Go on. Get up there.

1046
01:30:35,037 --> 01:30:38,529
I got ten bucks that
says you're mine!

1047
01:30:38,607 --> 01:30:42,099
- Buster, I got your first victim.
- Come up here!

1048
01:30:48,484 --> 01:30:51,851
All right! What am I bid
for this fine specimen?

1049
01:30:51,921 --> 01:30:53,548
Five dollars!

1050
01:30:53,622 --> 01:30:55,715
The bidding has begun
at five dollars.

1051
01:30:55,791 --> 01:30:58,692
- Ten dollars!
- Fifteen!

1052
01:30:58,761 --> 01:31:00,888
- Twenty!
- Twenty-five!

1053
01:31:00,963 --> 01:31:03,158
- Thirty!
- Thirty-five!

1054
01:31:03,232 --> 01:31:05,257
- Forty!
- Forty-five!

1055
01:31:05,334 --> 01:31:08,201
- Fifty!
- Fifty-five!

1056
01:31:08,270 --> 01:31:11,262
- Sixty!
- I'm bid sixty. Do I hear more?

1057
01:31:15,144 --> 01:31:18,341
Three hundred and thirty-nine dollars
and eighty-eight cents!

1058
01:31:23,119 --> 01:31:26,179
We can't accept any more bids.
That's sold...

1059
01:31:26,255 --> 01:31:29,918
to the little lady for $339.88!

1060
01:31:30,993 --> 01:31:32,426
Congratulations.

1061
01:31:40,503 --> 01:31:42,437
Okay, bachelors!
Who's next?

1062
01:31:52,481 --> 01:31:56,144
All right!
What am I bid for this guy?.

1063
01:31:56,218 --> 01:31:58,209
Do I hear a buck and a half?.

1064
01:31:58,287 --> 01:32:00,551
Anybody?.

1065
01:32:00,623 --> 01:32:03,649
- Seventy-five cents?
- I bid two bits!

1066
01:32:03,726 --> 01:32:06,661
Sold to the lady
for twenty-five cents!

1067
01:32:06,729 --> 01:32:08,356
I got him!

1068
01:32:16,739 --> 01:32:19,435
Phil Connors!
I thought that was you!

1069
01:32:19,508 --> 01:32:22,238
This is Ned Ryerson,
my new insurance agent.

1070
01:32:22,311 --> 01:32:23,744
I'll say!

1071
01:32:24,814 --> 01:32:26,907
I have not seen this guy
for 20 years.

1072
01:32:26,982 --> 01:32:29,951
He comes to me and buys whole life,
term, uniflex...

1073
01:32:30,019 --> 01:32:32,044
fire, theft, auto,
dental, health...

1074
01:32:32,121 --> 01:32:35,318
with the optional death
and dismemberment plan, water damage.

1075
01:32:35,391 --> 01:32:37,791
This is the best day of my life.

1076
01:32:37,860 --> 01:32:40,055
Mine too.

1077
01:32:40,129 --> 01:32:43,360
- Where are we going?
- Let's not spoil lt.

1078
01:32:46,268 --> 01:32:47,701
I got that!

1079
01:32:50,706 --> 01:32:54,198
- Why can't I look?
- Because you bother me a lot.

1080
01:32:54,276 --> 01:32:57,734
I'm getting cold.
How much longer do I have to sit here?

1081
01:32:57,813 --> 01:33:01,476
I'm just giving you your money's worth.
You paid top dollar for me.

1082
01:33:01,550 --> 01:33:04,383
I think you were a bargain.

1083
01:33:04,453 --> 01:33:07,354
Sweet of you to say.
You're probably right.

1084
01:33:10,159 --> 01:33:12,787
- Is It finished yet?
- Almost.

1085
01:33:12,862 --> 01:33:16,696
I still have to put cherry syrup on top
and then we can eat lt.

1086
01:33:16,765 --> 01:33:19,461
Come on!
I'm freezing!

1087
01:33:19,535 --> 01:33:22,402
One second. All right.
Let me turn toward the light.

1088
01:33:28,911 --> 01:33:30,378
It's amazing.

1089
01:33:31,080 --> 01:33:33,014
It's beautiful.

1090
01:33:36,652 --> 01:33:40,520
- How did you do that?
- I know your face so well...

1091
01:33:40,589 --> 01:33:42,648
I could have done It
with my eyes closed.

1092
01:33:47,296 --> 01:33:51,232
It's lovely.
I don't know what to say.

1093
01:33:52,468 --> 01:33:53,901
I do

1094
01:33:55,671 --> 01:33:58,162
No matter what happens tomorrow...

1095
01:33:58,240 --> 01:34:00,265
or for the rest of my life...

1096
01:34:00,342 --> 01:34:04,108
I'm happy now
because I love you.

1097
01:34:05,814 --> 01:34:07,748
I think I'm happy too.

1098
01:35:06,275 --> 01:35:08,869
- Please, not again.
- That is a great song!

1099
01:35:08,944 --> 01:35:10,571
- It's not!
- Don't listen to this man--

1100
01:35:12,748 --> 01:35:15,080
It's too early.

1101
01:35:25,594 --> 01:35:27,960
Something is different.

1102
01:35:28,030 --> 01:35:29,497
Good or bad?

1103
01:35:29,565 --> 01:35:32,056
Anything different is good...

1104
01:35:34,336 --> 01:35:36,497
but this could be real good.

1105
01:35:41,410 --> 01:35:43,344
Why are you here?

1106
01:35:43,412 --> 01:35:45,812
I bought you. I own you.

1107
01:35:47,850 --> 01:35:49,784
But why are you still here?

1108
01:35:49,852 --> 01:35:52,548
You said stay, so I stayed.

1109
01:35:55,524 --> 01:35:57,788
I said stay, so you stayed?

1110
01:35:57,860 --> 01:36:00,556
I can't even make a collie stay.

1111
01:36:02,498 --> 01:36:05,296
I gotta check something.

1112
01:36:05,367 --> 01:36:06,800
Stay.

1113
01:36:13,776 --> 01:36:15,209
They're gone!

1114
01:36:16,111 --> 01:36:18,170
They're all gone!

1115
01:36:19,748 --> 01:36:22,581
- Do you know what today is?
- What?

1116
01:36:23,919 --> 01:36:26,319
Today is tomorrow.

1117
01:36:26,388 --> 01:36:28,083
It happened.

1118
01:36:30,025 --> 01:36:32,220
- You're here.
- I'm here.

1119
01:36:36,165 --> 01:36:40,761
Why weren't you like this last night?
You just fell sleep,

1120
01:36:42,938 --> 01:36:45,429
It was the end
of a very long day.

1121
01:36:48,811 --> 01:36:52,440
Is there anything
I can do for you today?.

1122
01:36:52,514 --> 01:36:55,847
I'm sure I can think
of something.

1123
01:37:29,251 --> 01:37:31,185
It's so beautiful!

1124
01:37:41,830 --> 01:37:43,764
Let's live here.

1125
01:37:53,942 --> 01:37:56,035
We'll rent to start.
